# min-heap priority_queue

**Description** : priority_queue that arranges elements in ascending order.

**Syntax** : priority_queue<type, vector<type>, greater<type>> pq; 

**Example**:
``` cpp

   // create a priority queue of int
  // arranges elements in ascending order
  std::priority_queue<int, vector<int>, greater<int>> numbers;

  // add items to priority_queue
  numbers.push(1);
  numbers.push(20);
  numbers.push(7);

  // print element with highest priority
  cout << "Top element: " << numbers.top();


```


